      "patchset_number": 1,
      "message": "Thanks, John!  I checked our ci-management config and saw that we're specifying mvn-version: mvn38, which should be fine for now (we might need to upgrade to men 3.9 soon though .. I think one of the upcoming ODL releases requires that).  \n\nThat parameter only seems to apply to the Jenkins-based verifies.  This one that's failing is on GitHub.  I created an LF support ticket asking how to specify the minimum required version for maven on GitHub.",
